    "body": "Thanks for the report @moshe-blox, tagging @rkapka to help find a good path forward on this one. I don't think setting the timeout in that specific line would help, but rather we could add change the function where we add the 2 min timeout:\r\n```go\r\nfunc (m *ApiProxyMiddleware) ProxyRequest(req *http.Request) (*http.Response, ErrorJson)\r\n```\r\nto instead have some ugly conditional check for the `events` endpoint, and add a timeout of 0 if that's the case. Alternatively, we could check if the request headers include the event-stream header and do that instead, as that might be more reliable",
